**Cyberpunk, Hiper Realistic, Hiper Detailed. Jack "Iron" Johnson was born in 2315 in a small mining colony in one of the furthest regions of the galaxy. He showed an innate interest in technology from a young age and often watched his father repair vehicles and tools used in the mine. At six years old, he accompanied his father to the mine and when a system failed, he asked if he could help fix it. He quickly repaired the machinery and from that day on became his father's assistant in the mine, learning everything he knew about engineering and technology. As Jack grew up, he discovered his innate ability to understand technology and became fascinated with designing complex systems that could sustain life in space. After studying engineering at the University of Science and Technology in the galactic capital, Jack was quickly hired as a systems engineer at a space technology company, where he excelled in solving complex technical problems. One day, while working on a project, he received a call from his mother asking him to fix an old robot that had stopped working. Jack returned to his hometown, where he found that nothing had changed and was happy to be home for a while. After an accident, Jack tried to move his arm and leg, but they didn't respond. He then designed and built advanced prosthetics that allowed him to regain much of his mobility. Jack worked for hours to improve his prosthetics and created lighter, more durable, and easier-to-use prosthetics. --ar 3:2** - <@1080040680841285632> (fast)
